Pipelines are often used to perform complex operations on data. It is possible
to put several commands together into a pipeline. Frequently, the commands
used this way are referred to as filters. Filters take input, change it
somehow, and then output it. The first one we will try is sort. Imagine we
want to make a combined list of all of the executable programs in /bin and
/usr/bin, put them in sorted order, and then view the list